caption.text:
#JANGANJAIM
Well, what can I say more than how grateful and thankful to have them as my mentees! I am feeling very very blessed for the opportunity on being a mentor to them during UPH FEST, being a mentor taught me so much, that I, being my very best EVERY SINGLE DAY, to serve them, to make them feel comfortable, enjoying the session, waking them up, getting them to know about being a university student and also making them relize that they are mature enough, strong enough to deal with it. For a moment I was frustated, am I prepared enough? Am I good enough to lead them? Do I have all the knowledge to tell them? So many questions i've been asking myself, but i finally know, THEY ARE READY to face another step of education, for themself, and for the world! So, thankyou my mentees for making my days in mentoring one of the most unforgetable moment in my life! Go ahead champs! I'll be on your back if you need me :)
Remember! I will not always be your mentor, get yourself a better mentor once you got better than me, i am your mentor right now, your friend for all the time in the earth, your brother always, and I love you all with all my heart ‚ù§Ô∏è
